In the following document, saliency mappings of tokens for one sentence for each trigger word is shown. For each trained model, the mapping for each trigger word is done for the original sentence (with triggers), the sentence with triggers removed and the sentence with triggers changed to a synonym (triggers synonymized). Additionally, the actual label (label) and the label predicted by the model (prediction) is shown. The labeling for Huggingface transformers is used. As a result, “0” means the ending is true and “1” means the ending is false.
